trans-unit.source: Base class for all the chart elements.
The ChartElement class represents the most basic element of the chart element hierarchy.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartElement"></xref> class.
Releases the resources used by the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartElement"></xref>.
Releases the unmanaged resources used by the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartElement"></xref> and optionally releases the managed resources.

<xref uid="langword_csharp_True" name="True" href=""></xref> to release both managed and unmanaged resources; <xref uid="langword_csharp_False" name="False" href=""></xref> to release only unmanaged resources.
Determines whether the specified <xref:System.Object> is equal to the current <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartElement"></xref>.
The <xref:System.Object> to compare with the current <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartElement"></xref>.

<xref uid="langword_csharp_True" name="True" href=""></xref> if the specified <xref:System.Object> is equal to the current <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartElement"></xref>; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_False" name="False" href=""></xref>.
Returns a hash function for a particular type.
An <xref uid="langword_csharp_integer" name="integer" href=""></xref> value that represents the hash code for the current <xref:System.Object>.
Gets or sets an object associated with this chart element.
The Tag property can be used to store additional data with this chart element.
An <xref:System.Object> associated with this chart element.
Returns a string that represents the current <xref:System.Object>.
A <xref uid="langword_csharp_string" name="string" href=""></xref> value that represents the current <xref:System.Object>.
